1. Lab Information
Lab Title: JetBrains Lab
Course: Network Forensics

2. Objective
With the help of applications like Wireshark, NetworkMiner, and Brim, the primary aim was to:

— Ascertain the source IP address of the attacker.
— Establish the vulnerable service and corresponding CVE.
— Monitor the activities of the adversary post-compromise.
— Find out about any persistence techniques such as web shells and backdoors.
— Examine attacker commands and post-compromise actions.
— Relate observed behaviors to the MITRE ATT&CK framework

